\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01SpaGDsZErPX8fkBwjwQ5UB\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"{\\\"body\\\":\\\"## Problem\\\\n\\\\nWhen `entire enable` runs, `EnsureMetadataBranch()` creates the local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch. Previously it only checked if the local branch existed — if not, it created an empty orphan. This shadowed the remote-tracking branch (`origin/entire/checkpoints/v1`) that `getSessionsBranchTree()` would otherwise fall back to, breaking `entire explain` and other checkpoint lookups with \\\\\\\"checkpoint not found\\\\\\\".\\\\n\\\\n**Reproduction:**\\\\n1. `git clone` a repo that has `entire/checkpoints/v1` on the remote\\\\n2. `entire explain --commit <hash>` → works (falls back to remote ref)\\\\n3. `entire enable` → creates empty orphan local branch\\\\n4. `entire explain --commit <hash>` → fails (finds empty local branch, never falls back to remote)\\\\n\\\\n## Fix\\\\n\\\\n`EnsureMetadataBranch()` now handles three scenarios:\\\\n\\\\n1. **Local branch doesn't exist, remote does** → create local from remote\\\\n2. **Local branch exists but is empty orphan, remote has data** → update local from remote\\\\n3. **No local or remote branch** → create empty orphan (unchanged)\\\\n\\\\nNon-empty local branches are never overwritten.\\\\n\\\\n## Test plan\\\\n\\\\n- [x] `TestEnsureMetadataBranch/creates_from_remote_on_fresh_clone`\\\\n- [x] `TestEnsureMetadataBranch/updates_empty_orphan_from_remote`\\\\n- [x] `TestEnsureMetadataBranch/creates_empty_orphan_when_no_remote`\\\\n- [x] Verified end-to-end on `git clone git@github.com:entireio/cli`: explain works before and after enable\\\\n\\\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"fix: enable preserves remote checkpoint data on local metadata branch\\\"}\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"uuid\":\"7b74befd-1625-4ba7-937e-054d0e9b98c3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-26T05:13:48.673Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"stdout\":\"{\\\"body\\\":\\\"## Problem\\\\n\\\\nWhen `entire enable` runs, `EnsureMetadataBranch()` creates the local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch. Previously it only checked if the local branch existed — if not, it created an empty orphan. This shadowed the remote-tracking branch (`origin/entire/checkpoints/v1`) that `getSessionsBranchTree()` would otherwise fall back to, breaking `entire explain` and other checkpoint lookups with \\\\\\\"checkpoint not found\\\\\\\".\\\\n\\\\n**Reproduction:**\\\\n1. `git clone` a repo that has `entire/checkpoints/v1` on the remote\\\\n2. `entire explain --commit <hash>` → works (falls back to remote ref)\\\\n3. `entire enable` → creates empty orphan local branch\\\\n4. `entire explain --commit <hash>` → fails (finds empty local branch, never falls back to remote)\\\\n\\\\n## Fix\\\\n\\\\n`EnsureMetadataBranch()` now handles three scenarios:\\\\n\\\\n1. **Local branch doesn't exist, remote does** → create local from remote\\\\n2. **Local branch exists but is empty orphan, remote has data** → update local from remote\\\\n3. **No local or remote branch** → create empty orphan (unchanged)\\\\n\\\\nNon-empty local branches are never overwritten.\\\\n\\\\n## Test plan\\\\n\\\\n- [x] `TestEnsureMetadataBranch/creates_from_remote_on_fresh_clone`\\\\n- [x] `TestEnsureMetadataBranch/updates_empty_orphan_from_remote`\\\\n- [x] `TestEnsureMetadataBranch/creates_empty_orphan_when_no_remote`\\\\n- [x] Verified end-to-end on `git clone git@github.com:entireio/cli`: explain works before and after enable\\\\n\\\\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"fix: enable preserves remote checkpoint data on local metadata branch\\\"}\",\"stderr\":\"\",\"interrupted\":false,\"isImage\":false,\"noOutputExpected\":false},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"335f893b-73ab-455a-a2b1-70c5162662d5\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"7b74befd-1625-4ba7-937e-054d0e9b98c3\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/dvydra/src/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"229c0af5-5604-44a0-a6ae-795